# <%= @current_collective.name %>'s Funding Pool

Each LLM call an attached agent makes is billed to one enrolled member's own prepaid balance, chosen at random per call, so cost spreads roughly evenly over time across the enrolled members who have balance available. The pool never holds money.
<% if @funding_pool.archived? %>

**This pool is closed.** Its agents stop running and no balances are being drawn on; everything resumes automatically if it reopens. Enrollments are kept in case it does; withdrawal is still available.
<% elsif !@funding_pools_enabled %>

**Funding pools are currently disabled for this collective.** No balances are being drawn on; enrollment is paused. Withdrawal is still available.
<% end %>

| | |
|---------|-------|
| Status | <%= @funding_pool.archived? ? "Closed" : "Open" %> |
| Pool draw ceiling | <%= format("$%.2f", @funding_pool.member_draw_cap_cents / 100.0) %> per member per <%= @funding_pool.member_draw_cap_period %> (UTC) |
| Enrolled members | <%= @pool_enrollments.any? ? @pool_enrollments.map { |e| "[#{e.user.display_name}](#{e.user.path})" }.join(", ") : "(none yet)" %> |
<% enrolled_user_ids = @pool_enrollments.map(&:user_id) -%>
| Funded agents | <%= @funded_agents.any? ? @funded_agents.map { |a| "[#{a.display_name}](#{a.path})#{" (not running — principal not enrolled)" unless a.parent_id && enrolled_user_ids.include?(a.parent_id)}" }.join(", ") : "(none yet)" %> |
| Your enrollment | <%= @current_user_enrolled ? format("Enrolled — this pool's agents can draw from your prepaid balance, up to your own ceiling of $%.2f per %s (or the pool's ceiling, whichever is lower)", @current_user_enrollment.draw_cap_cents / 100.0, @current_user_enrollment.draw_cap_period) : "Not enrolled" %> |
| Spend (last 30 days) | <%= format("$%.2f", @usage_report[:total_cents].to_f / 100) %> |
<% if @usage_report[:pending_count] > 0 -%>
| Calls in flight | <%= @usage_report[:pending_count] %><%= " (#{@usage_report[:stale_pending_count]} stale)" if @usage_report[:stale_pending_count] > 0 %> |
<% end -%>
<% if @usage_report[:member_rows].any? { |r| r[:spend_cents].to_f > 0 } -%>

Member spend (last 30 days):
<% @usage_report[:member_rows].each do |row| -%>
<% next if row[:spend_cents].to_f <= 0 -%>
* <%= row[:user].display_name %><%= " (withdrawn)" unless @pool_enrollments.any? { |e| e.user_id == row[:user].id } %> — <%= format("$%.2f", row[:spend_cents].to_f / 100) %>
<% end -%>
<% end -%>
<% if @usage_report[:agent_rows].any? -%>

Agent spend (last 30 days):
<% @usage_report[:agent_rows].each do |row| -%>
* <%= row[:agent].display_name %> — <%= format("$%.2f", row[:spend_cents].to_f / 100) %>
<% end -%>
<% end -%>

The pool stops drawing from a member once its draws from them reach the ceiling for the <%= @funding_pool.member_draw_cap_period %>; each member also sets their own ceiling when enrolling, and the lower of the two applies. Ceilings are per pool — draws by other pools count against those pools' ceilings, not this one's.

Enrolling is consenting to fund this collective's agents from your own prepaid balance, up to a ceiling you state yourself over a day, week, or month; it requires prepaid credits, and you can withdraw at any time. Withdrawal drops you out of draws immediately. To change your ceiling, enroll again with the new value. Admins manage the pool itself (lifecycle, pool ceiling, attached agents) from the collective's settings.
